**Study ID:** ${shortId}
**Lead investigator(s):** ${lead}
**Version:** ${version}
**Design:** Multi-national active-comparator new-user (ACNU) cohort study under a target trial emulation framework${s.emulatedTrial ? ` (emulating ${s.emulatedTrial})` : ""}.

The active comparator is used as an emulated placebo arm; a drug class with similar indication, similar temporal trends in use, and no known a priori association with the outcome of interest. This minimises confounding by indication and addresses immortal-time / prevalent-user bias by anchoring follow-up at the moment of treatment commencement, similar to randomisation in a target RCT (Hernán & Robins 2016).

